<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880818-0031 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: S.A.Y. Industries Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> SAYI </CO><IN> DIV </IN><TEXT>   S.A.Y. Industries Inc., Leominster, Mass., said shareholders approved its previously announced plan to spin off its S.A.Y. Packaging Inc. unit into a new publicly traded company.    S.A.Y. Industries said shareholders of record at the close of business on Sept. 2 will receive one share of the new company for each S.A.Y. Industries common share owned.    Upon completion of the spinoff, S.A.Y. Industries will change its name to Scribe Systems Inc. and will focus on its desktop publishing and corporate electronic businesses. The new company will continue to make plastic containers for the petroleum industry. </TEXT></DOC>